==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refreshment
<hw>Re*fresh"ment</hw> <pr>(-m<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[CF. OF. <ets>refreschissement</ets>, F.
<ets>rafra⟦icir⟧chissement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
refreshing, or the state of being refreshed; restoration of strength,
spirit, vigor, or liveliness; relief after suffering; new life or
animation after depression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which refreshes; means of restoration or
reanimation; especially, an article of food or drink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refret</ent>⟦br⟧
